    <thetext>In bug 440477 I implemented merging of extra classpath attributes from a container and its elements during classpath resolution.

In bug 465293 we see that this implementation applies undesirable precedence: Individual attributes are not merged but copied into a bigger list, and in this implementation attributes from the elements come before attributes of the referring entry.

This is in conflict with the intuition that per-project configuration should override per-workspace configuration.

On the long run we may want to filter duplicate attributes, but since I&apos;m not aware of a specification saying that this should happen, for 4.5 I&apos;m just changing the order in which attributes appear in the combined list: explicit per project configuration (from the referring entry) to come before container-provided configuration. For external null annotation paths this establishes the desired semantics.</thetext>
